Rating: 3
This dish is similar to my favorite never-fail treatment of veal chops, and works beautifully with pork chops as well. Remove the wine from this recipe and use just a splash of balsamic vinegar (I use Lulu's Fig Balsamic), and rub the combined ingredients all over your chops. No need to bathe the chops in a pool of liquid - just enough olive oil and balsamic to coat and moisten them. A bit of sage or thyme also enhances the flavor nicely. I honestly believe that leaving out the wine elevates this recipe to four forks.

