Rating: 3
Welcome summer! With apologies to George (Foreman), this dish demands outdoor cooking. The slight smokiness and caramelization imparted by a really hot gas or charcoal fire lend flavor notes that complement the garlic and rosemary. I substituted 2 Tbl. balsamic vinegar for the wine, which I think helps with the browning without being either too sweet or too sour. I agree that the timing is a bit too short: 5-7 min. per side, depending on thickness, is more reasonable. Served with a salad, pasta with basil pesto, and a nice Chianti Classico. Molto delizioso!

